4 SYNOPSIS:
5 Under existing law, the Alabama Workforce Board
6 may consist of up to 40 members.
7 This bill would increase the maximum number of
8 board members to 45.
9 This bill would establish a quorum of four
10 voting members of the Alabama Workforce Board Executive
11 Committee to do business and make decisions.
12 This bill would allow members of the executive
13 committee to participate in meetings by electronic
14 means, including for voting and establishing a quorum.
15 Under existing law, a regional workforce board
16 may consist of up to 20 members.
17 This bill would increase the maximum number of
18 required workforce board members to 25.
19 This bill would also make nonsubstantive,
20 technical revisions to update the existing code
21 language to current style.
22
23
24 A BILL
25 TO BE ENTITLED
26 AN ACT
27
28 Relating to the Alabama Workforce Board; to amend
