29 Sections 25-15-3, 25-15-5, and 25-15-7; to increase the number
30 of board members on the Alabama Workforce Board; to establish
31 a quorum of voting members for the executive committee; to
32 allow members of the executive committee to participate in
33 meetings by electronic means; to increase the number of board
34 members on a regional workforce board; and to make
35 nonsubstantive, technical revisions to update the existing
36 code language to current style.
37 BE IT ENACTED BY THE LEGISLATURE OF ALABAMA:
38 Section 1. Sections 25-15-3, 25-15-5, and 25-15-7 are
39 amended to read as follows:
40 "§25-15-3
41 (a) The Alabama Workforce Board shall consist of no
42 more than 4045 members, or their designees, and meet the
43 membership criteria established by WIOA. All members, unless
44 otherwise provided in this subsection, shall be appointed by
45 the Governor, subject to confirmation by the Senate. A
46 majority of members shall be representatives of business and
47 industry, at least one of which shall represent small
48 business. Twenty percent of the members shall be
49 representatives of workforce, including two labor
50 representatives and one apprenticeship program representative.
51 The board shall also include one representative of the WIOA
52 Title I-b programs; the State Adult Education Director; one
53 representative of the Wagner-Peyser Program; the Commissioner
54 of the Alabama Department of Rehabilitation Services; the
55 Chancellor of the Alabama Community College System; the
56 Secretary of Workforce; one member of the Alabama Senate
Page 2

Secretary of Workforce; one member of the Alabama Senate
HB477 INTRODUCED
57 appointed by the presiding officer of the Senate; one member
58 of the Alabama House of Representatives appointed by the
59 Speaker of the House of Representatives; one county
60 commissioner appointed by the Governor; one mayor appointed by
61 the Governor; and the Governor or his or her designee. The
62 overall membership of the board shall be inclusive and reflect
63 the racial, gender, geographic, urban/, rural, and economic
64 diversity of the state.
65 (b) The Governor shall appoint a chair from the
66 business representatives on the board as set forth in WIOA. In
67 addition, the Governor shall appoint a vice chair from the
68 business representatives on the board.
69 (c) The Governor shall establish bylaws governing the
70 membership and activities of the board as required by WIOA and
71 its implementing regulations, including 20 C.F.R. §
72 679.110(d).
73 (d) Members may serve no more than two four-year terms
74 as provided in the bylaws established pursuant to subsection
75 (c)."
76 "§25-15-5
77 (a) There is established the Executive Committee of the
78 Alabama Workforce Board which shall be comprised of seven
79 voting members, including the Governor or the Governor's
80 designee, the Chair of the Alabama Workforce Board, and five
81 executive level business leaders who shall be appointed by the
82 Governor, and who may or may not be members of the Alabama
83 Workforce Board. The Secretary of Workforce shall serve as a
84 non-voting ex officio member of the executive committee.
