85 (b) Four voting members of the executive committee
86 shall constitute a quorum for the purpose of transacting
87 business, and decisions shall be made on the basis of a
88 majority of the quorum then present and voting.
89 (c) Members of the executive committee may participate
90 in meetings in person or by means of telephone, video
91 conference, or other similar communications equipment, so that
92 all individuals participating in the meeting may hear each
93 other at the same time. Participation by electronic means
94 shall constitute in person presence at a meeting for all
95 purposes, including for purposes of voting and establishing a
96 quorum.
97 (b)(d)(1) The appointed members of the executive
98 committee shall be appointed to serve a five-year term,
99 provided that the initial appointees' terms shall be
100 designated by the Governor as follows: one member shall serve
101 a term of one year, one member shall serve a term of two
102 years, one member shall serve a term of three years, one
103 member shall serve a term of four years, and one member shall
104 serve a term of five years.
105 (2) Any appointed member may be re-appointed, but no
106 appointed member may serve on the executive committee for more
107 than a total of 10 consecutive years from the date of initial
108 appointment. Terms shall begin on July 1 of the first year of
109 the appointed member's term and end on June 30 of the final
110 year of that member's term.
111 (3) Notwithstanding subdivision (2), appointed members
112 of the executive committee may continue to serve after the
