134 "§25-15-7
135 (a) At the direction of the Governor, the Secretary of
136 Workforce shall establish seven regional workforce boards to
137 serve as Alabama's local workforce development boards for
138 purposes of Section 107 of the Workforce Innovation and
139 Opportunity Act of 2014 (P.L. 113-128), as amended, 29 U.S.C.
140 § 3122. The Department of Workforce shall establish bylaws
Page 5

§ 3122. The Department of Workforce shall establish bylaws
HB477 INTRODUCED
141 governing the membership and activities of the regional
142 workforce boards in compliance with WIOA. The local workforce
143 development boards shall be certified by the Governor pursuant
144 to 29 U.S.C. § 3122(a).
145 (b) The Secretary of Workforce shall establish
146 geographic boundaries of the regional workforce boards and
147 criteria for the appointment of members to the regional
148 workforce boards consistent with WIOA, including 29 U.S.C. §
149 3122 and 20 C.F.R. § 679.110. One such criterion shall be a
150 duty for an appointing official to consult with the Secretary
151 of Workforce before making an appointment to a regional
152 workforce board.
153 (c) The Department of Workforce may adopt rules
154 pursuant to the Alabama Administrative Procedure Act to carry
155 out this section.
156 (d) A regional workforce board shall perform the
157 functions set forth in WIOA, including each of the following:
158 (1) Develop a local plan as provided in WIOA,
159 consistent with the WIOA State Plan and the Strategic
160 Workforce Plan.
161 (2) Publish, for core and partner agency and public
162 use, workforce research and regional labor market analysis
163 using primary state labor market information provided by the
164 department.
165 (3) Convene local workforce development system
166 stakeholders to assist in the development of the local plan.
167 (4) Lead local efforts to engage with a diverse range
168 of employers.
