169 (5) Lead local efforts to develop and implement career
170 pathways.
171 (6) Lead local efforts to identify and promote
172 promising workforce development strategies.
173 (7) Lead local efforts to integrate data and technology
174 systems.
175 (e) A regional workforce board shall submit an annual
176 budget request to the Secretary of Workforce and the executive
177 committee that is consistent with the Strategic Workforce
178 Plan. A regional workforce board's annual budget submission
179 shall demonstrate that the membership of the board satisfies
180 the relevant WIOA state workforce development board membership
181 requirements, including the requirements set forth in 29
182 U.S.C. § 3122 and 20 C.F.R. § 679.320. The membership of any
183 regional workforce board may not exceed twenty25 members. A
184 regional workforce development board may not expend state or
185 federal workforce development funds except pursuant to a
186 categorical annual budget approved by the Secretary of
187 Workforce."
188 Section 2. This act shall become effective on October
